y (Cameroon)|National Day]], creation of a unitary state in 1972\n|-\n|{{flag|Canada}} ||data-sort-value=\"07/01\"|1 July||[[Canada Day]], creation of a federal Canada from three British Dominions in 1867\n|-\n|style=\"background:pink\"|{{flag|Catalonia}} ([[Spain]]) ||data-sort-value=\"09/11\"|11 September||[[National Day of Catalonia|National Day]], commemorates the [[Siege of Barcelona (1713\u201314)|fall of Barcelona]] during the [[War of the Spanish Succession]] in 1714\n|-\n|{{flag|Cape Verde}} ||data-sort-value=\"07/05\"|5 July||Independence from [[Portugal]] in 1975\n|-\n|style=\"background:pink\"|{{flag|Cayman Islands}} ([[United Kingdom]]) ||data-sort-value=\"07/01\"<!--Updated for 2019-->|1st Monday in July||\n|-\n|{{flag|Central African Republic}} ||data-sort-value=\"12/01\"|1 December||Made an autonomous territory within the [[French Community]] in 1958\n|-\n|{{flag|Chad}} ||data-sort-value=\"08/11\"|11 August||Independence from France in 1960\n|-\n|{{flag|Chile}} ||data-sort-value=\"09/18\"|18 September||[[Government Junta of Chile (1810)|The first Government Junta]] is created in 1810\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|China}} [[China|People's Republic of China]] ||data-sort-value=\"10/01\"|1 October||[[National Day of the People's Republic of China]] (Proclamation of the People's Republic of China in 1949)\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |{{flagdeco|Republic of China}} [[Taiwan|Republic of China]] ||data-sort-value=\"01/01\"|1 January||Founding Day of the Republic of China, establishment of the [[Provisional Government of the Republic of China (1912)|Provisional Government]] in 1912\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"10/10\"|10 October||[[Double Ten Day]] commemorating the 1911 [[Wuchang Uprising]] that led to abolishment of the monarchy and founding of the Republic in China in 1911\n|-\n|{{flag|Colombia}} ||data-sort-value=\"07/20\"|20 July||[[Colombian Declaration of Independence|Declaration of independence]] from Spain in 1810\n|-\n|{{flag|Comoros}} ||data-sort-value=\"07/06\"|6 July||In