nezuela}} ||data-sort-value=\"07/05\"|5 July||Independence Day, [[Venezuelan Declaration of Independence|declaration of independence]] from Spain in 1811\n|-\n|{{flag|Vietnam}} ||data-sort-value=\"09/02\"|2 September||National Day, declaration of independence from France and Japan in 1945\n|-\n|style=\"background:pink\"|{{flag|Wales}} ([[United Kingdom]]) ||data-sort-value=\"03/01\"|1 March||[[St. David's Day]], feast day of patron saint of Wales\n|-\n|style=\"background:pink\"|{{flag|Wallonia}} ([[Belgium]]) ||data-sort-value=\"09/15\"|third Sunday of September||[[Day of the Walloon Region]]\n|-\n|{{flag|Yemen}} ||data-sort-value=\"05/22\"|22 May||[[Unity Day (Yemen)|Unity Day]], [[Yemen Arab Republic|North]] and [[South Yemen]] are unified as the [[Republic of Yemen]] in 1990\n|-\n|{{flag|Zambia}} ||data-sort-value=\"10/24\"|24 October||Independence Day, declaration of independence from the United Kingdom in 1964\n|-\n|{{flag|Zimbabwe}} ||data-sort-value=\"04/18\"|18 April||Granting of independence by the United Kingdom in 1980; it had previously [[Rhodesia's Unilateral Declaration of Independence|declared independence]] as [[Rhodesia]] on 11 November 1965\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Holidays}}\n* [[Public holiday]]\n* [[Flag Day]]\n* [[Independence Day]]\n* [[Liberation Day]]\n* [[Civil religion]]\n* [[National holiday (disambiguation)|National Holiday]]\n* [[F\u00eate nationale]]\n* [[Republic Day]]\n* [[Victory Day]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:National days| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of observances]]\n[[Category:Types of national holidays]]\n[[Category:January observances]]\n[[Category:February observances]]\n[[Category:March observances]]\n[[Category:April observances]]\n[[Category:May observances]]\n[[Category:June observances]]<!--Please do not remove this category as redundant, there are both fixed and movable observances on here-->\n[[Category:July observances]]\n[[Category:August observances]]\n[[Category:September observances]]\n[[Category:October observances]]\n[[Category:November observances]]\n[[Category:December observances]]\n[[Category:Holidays and observances by scheduling (nth weekday of the month)]]\n[[Category:Lists of national symbols|Day]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Designated date on which celebrations mark the nationhood of a nation}}\n{{About|celebrations of nationhood|holidays with names like \"National Item Day\"|List of commemorative days}}\n{{original research|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n\n[[File:Independence of Brazil 1888.jpg|upright=1.4|thumb|''[[Independence or Death (painting)|Independence or Death]]'', famous painting from [[Pedro Am\u00e9rico]] that celebrates the [[Independence Day (Brazil)|Independence Day]] of Brazil.]]\n[[File:Carl XVI Gustaf och Silvia p\u00e5 Skansen 2009.jpg|thumb|On ''Sveriges nationaldag'' in Sweden the King and Queen (in national costume) celebrate Sweden's independence each year on 6 June.]]\nA '''national day''' (or state day) is a designated date on which celebrations mark the [[nationhood]] of a [[nation]], [[Sovereign state|state]], nationality, or non-sovereign country.{{cn|date=February 2020}} This nationhood can be symbolized by the date of [[independence]], of becoming a republic or a significant date for a patron saint or a ruler (birthday, [[Accession Day|accession]], removal, etc.). Often the day is not called \"National Day\" but serves and can be considered as one. The national day will often be a [[Public holiday|national holiday]]. Many countries have more than one national day.\n\n==List of national days==\n{{see also|List of national independence days}}\n[[File:BlankMap-World6 national days.svg|right|thumb|upright=2.25|Map with reasons for national days]]\n{{clear}}\n\nRegions that are not broadly recognized [[sovereign state]]s are shown in ''pink''. For regions controlled by sovereign states (such as federal states, autonomous regions, or colonies), the name of the sovereign state is shown in parentheses.\n\nDays that are not fixed to the Gregorian calendar are sorted by their 2019 occurrences.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n|-\n!Nation\n!Date <!-- To sort properly needs a data-sort-value in the form mm/dd that matches the date, or is close if the date moves -->\n!class=\"unsortable\"|National day\n|-\n|{{flag|Afghanistan}} ||data-sort-value=\"08/19\"|19 August||[[Afghan Independence Day|Independence]] from United Kingdom control over Afghan foreign affairs in 1919. (see [[Afghan Independence Day]])\n|-\n|{{flag|Albania}} ||data-sort-value=\"11/28\"|28 November||[[Albanian Flag Day]]: Raising of the Albanian flag in [[Vlor\u00eb]] to announce the [[Albanian Declaration of Independence]] in 1912\n|-\n|style=\"background:pink\"|{{flag|Alderney}} ([[British Islands]]) ||data-sort-value=\"12/15\"|15 December||Homecoming Day, the return of the Islanders after the end of the [[German occupation of the Channel Islands]] during [[World War II]] 1945\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Algeria}} ||data-sort-value=\"11/01\"|1 November||Start of the [[Algerian War of Independence|War of Independence]] in 1954\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"07/05\"|5 July||[[Independence Day (Algeria)]] in 1962\n|-\n|style=\"background:pink\"|{{flag|American Samoa}} ([[United States]]) ||data-sort-value=\"04/17\"|17 April||[[Flag of the United States|US Flag]] Day, commemorates the date American Samoa became a US territory and first flew the US flag in 1900, as well as the date of adoption of the American Samoan flag in 1960.\n|-\n|{{flag|Andorra}} ||data-sort-value=\"09/08\"|8 September||[[Our Lady of Meritxell]] Day, [[patron saint]] of Andorra, signing of the [[Par\u00e9age of Andorra 1278]]\n|-\n|{{flag|Angola}} ||data-sort-value=\"11/11\"|11 November||Independence from Portugal in 1975\n|-\n|style=\"background:pink\"|{{flag|Anguilla}} ([[United Kingdom]]) ||data-sort-value=\"05/30\"|30 May||Anguilla Day; the beginning of the Anguillian Revolution in 1967\n|-\n|{{flag|Antigua an